      "id": "happy",
      "english": "happy",
      "word": "سعيد",
      "romanized": "sa'id",
      "grammarNote": "Arabic adjectives agree in gender: سعيد (sa'id, masc.) / سعيدة (sa'ida, fem.). They also agree in definiteness when modifying a noun: رجل سعيد (rajul sa'id = a happy man), الرجل السعيد (ar-rajul as-sa'id = the happy man). In predicate position ('I am happy'), the adjective is indefinite: أنا سعيد (ana sa'id).",
      "englishPhrase": "I'm very happy today.",
      "phrase": "أنا سعيد جداً اليوم.",
      "phraseRomanized": "ana sa'id jiddan al-yawm."
